The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, March 04, 2004 				 Patni Q4 net up 51% at Rs 63 crore
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, March 3: Patni Computers has posted a 51 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 62.94 crore for the fourth quarter ended December 31 against Rs 41.67 crore in the year-ago period.																								The companys full-year net profit rose 11.2 per cent to Rs 192.27 crore compared with Rs 172.86 crore in the previous year. 																								The board has declared a dividend of 50 per cent for all its shareholders, a company release said.																								Chairman and CEO Narendra K. Patni said, Our performance in 2003 highlights our unique business model. Our domain strengths in key verticals, and robust delivery capabilities combine to provide a growing business opportunity.																								Chief financial officer Deepak Sogani said the company was looking at more business with global firms and making continuous investments in sales, marketing, infrastructure and service capabilities.																								The companys global relationship with GE contributed over $100 million in 2003. 
